    "chemicalDescription": [
      "sr-Dog Polypeptide-4 is a single chain recombinant protein produced by fermentation in E. coli. The starting gene is synthesized to be identical to the gene which codes for Insulin-Like Growth Factor derived from dog. The parent protein contains a maximum of 153 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
